    "name": "Scott Hamilton",
    "profile": "American jazz tenor saxophone player.\r\n\r\nBorn : September 12, 1954 in Providence, Rhode Island.\r\n\r\nFrom the very beginning of his musical career in the mid 70's he was associated with the swing-revival scene which made him - for his age - a very unmodern artist. However - within that genre he was seen as the future and his smooth playing has been compared to great swing tenors like [a=Ben Webster]. Besides releasing his own records on the [l=Concord Jazz] label, he has lead the labels house band in many various settings, also backing vocalists like [a=Maxine Sullivan] and [a=Rosemary Clooney].\r\nHusband of [a= Manami Hamilton].\r\n",
